{% extends "base_rules_v2.j2" %}

{% block analysis_guidelines %}
Use horizontal levels as the main signal source:
1. BUY only after price has visibly rebounded/reflected from support, or after a breakout retest has already held.
2. SELL only after price has visibly rebounded/reflected from resistance, or after a breakdown retest has already failed.
3. Breakouts need a completed close beyond the level plus a visible retest/hold; do not anticipate the retest.
4. Rejections need wick/candle evidence at the level and enough remaining room to the next target.
5. Prefer fewer, HIGHER-QUALITY trades. HOLD if the setup is not visually obvious.
6. Use the wider context chart to reject local levels that are not meaningful in the larger structure.
7. Do not ask for a pullback entry. If the confirmed move is still early enough, choose market now; if late, HOLD.
{% endblock %}


